totalNumberOfEntries.name: totalNumberOfEntries
totalNumberOfEntries.description: Total number of logged entries for this chassis.

configTableEntry.name: configTableEntry
configTableEntry.description: Each entry allows a user to configure the alarm table for a specific slot. Objects such as Current Entry, MaxEntries Allowed, and an Enable/Disable switch are available.

slotInChassis.name: slotInChassis
slotInChassis.description: Each Slot can be separately configured. This is the slot number for the configuration entry.

numEntriesLoggeds.name: numEntriesLoggeds
numEntriesLoggeds.description: This is the total number of entries looged for this slot.

numEntriesRequested.name: numEntriesRequested
numEntriesRequested.description: Maximum number of entries to store before wrapping the log on this slot.

numEntriesAllocated.name: numEntriesAllocated
numEntriesAllocated.description: This is the number of entries allocated to log alarms on this slot. It will always be less than or equal to the requested number of entries.

lastLoggedEntryLogId.name: lastLoggedEntryLogId
lastLoggedEntryLogId.description: This is the log id of the last entry logged for this slot.

logCommand.name: logCommand
logCommand.description: Allows the user to send the log the commands specified in the enumeration.

wrap.name: wrap
wrap.description: This is whether or not this configuration has wrapped or not.

trapLogEntry.name: trapLogEntry
trapLogEntry.description: Each alarm entry is generated from one of the following sources; (1) a module in one of the main chassis slots, (2) the EM, (3) or a power supply.

logId.name: logId
logId.description: Each slot has a maximium number of log entries that it can support. Each entry is assigned a monotonically increasing sequence number. When the maximum number of entries for a slot is reached, the log wraps. Each new entry will replace the oldest entry for that slot.

nvmpId.name: nvmpId
nvmpId.description: This contains the nvmp id of the trap that occurred.

trapLogAcknowledged.name: trapLogAcknowledged
trapLogAcknowledged.description: This field is set to 2 if a trap as been acknowledged from the EM.

trapLogVarBind.name: trapLogVarBind
trapLogVarBind.description: This is an ASN.1 encoded string representing the pairs of OID/value items supplied in the original SNMP or NVMP trap.

trapLogDescription.name: trapLogDescription
trapLogDescription.description: This is an internally defined string used to describe an alarm. Its primary use is for display on the EMs LCD. A default value will be used for the old trap calls.

timeLogged.name: timeLogged
timeLogged.description: The time the entry was logged. This will be date and time if possible.

filterId.name: filterId
filterId.description: This will be used to filter certain alarms. The criteria is TBD. An example of classification: informational - requires no intervention. warning - Does not require immediate intervention. e.g. static risk severe - Requires immediate intervention. e.g. power overload. fatal - Requires attention and module may take corrective action such as reboot. e.g. Unrecoverable software or hardware error.

trapOID.name: trapOID
trapOID.description: This OID combines the General Trap code, Specific Trap code, and the sys object id into one OID.

z80Time.name: z80Time
z80Time.description: This is the time that the Z80 has been up for the board that sent this trap.

filterEntry.name: filterEntry
filterEntry.description: Each filter entry is generated from one of the following sources; (1) a module in one of the main chassis slots, (2) the EM, (3) or a power supply.

filterLogId.name: filterLogId
filterLogId.description: Each slot has a maximum number of log entries that it can support. Each entry is assigned a monotonically increasing sequence number. When the maximum number of entries for a slot is reached, the log wraps. Each new entry willreplace the oldest entry for that slot.

filterNvmpId.name: filterNvmpId
filterNvmpId.description: This contains the nvmp id of the trap that was generated.

filterTrapLogAcknowledged.name: filterTrapLogAcknowledged
filterTrapLogAcknowledged.description: This field is non-zero if a trap has been acknowleged from the EM.

filterTrapLogVarBind.name: filterTrapLogVarBind
filterTrapLogVarBind.description: This is an ASN.1 encoded string representing the pairs of OID/value items supplied in the original SNMP or NVMP trap.

filterTrapLogDescription.name: filterTrapLogDescription
filterTrapLogDescription.description: This is an internally defined string used to describe an alarm. It's primary use is for display on the EMs LCD. A default value will be used for the old trap calls.

filterTimeLogged.name: filterTimeLogged
filterTimeLogged.description: The time the entry was logged. This will be date and time if possible.

filterFilterId.name: filterFilterId
filterFilterId.description: This will be used tofilter certain alarms. The criteria is TBD. An example of classification: informational-requires no intervention. warning - Does not require immediate intervention. e.g. statis risk severe - Requires immediate intervention. e.g. power overload. fatal - Requires attention and module may take corrective action such as reboot. e.g. Unrecoverale software or hardware error.

filterTrapOID.name: filterTrapOID
filterTrapOID.description: This OID combines the General Trap code, Specific Trap code, and the sys object id into one OID.

filterZ80Time.name: filterZ80Time
filterZ80Time.description: The number of time ticks that have passed since this boards Z80 processor has been up.

trapLoggerAgent.name: trapLoggerAgent
trapLoggerAgent.description: Reflects the operational status of the traplogger agent
